= TeaLauncher =

Windows Simple Keystroke Launcher.


= Building with .NET 8 =

== Installation ==

Install .NET 8 SDK:

Linux:
  wget https://dot.net/v1/dotnet-install.sh -O dotnet-install.sh
  chmod +x ./dotnet-install.sh
  ./dotnet-install.sh --channel 8.0

Windows:
  Download and install .NET 8 SDK from:
  https://dotnet.microsoft.com/download/dotnet/8.0

== Build Commands ==

Linux (cross-compile to Windows):
  dotnet build -r win-x64

Windows:
  dotnet build

== Test Commands ==

Run unit tests:
  dotnet test

== Publish Commands ==

Framework-dependent deployment (requires .NET 8 Desktop Runtime on target):
  dotnet publish -c Release -r win-x64

Self-contained deployment (no runtime required, larger size):
  dotnet publish -c Release -r win-x64 --self-contained -p:PublishSingleFile=true -p:IncludeNativeLibrariesForSelfExtract=true


== Usage ==

For framework-dependent builds, install .NET 8 Desktop Runtime:
  https://dotnet.microsoft.com/download/dotnet/8.0

run:
TeaLauncher.exe conf/my.conf

Press <Ctrl><Space> to show input window.
And, input command, press <Enter> to run the command.
You can use to complement command. You press <Tab> when inputting commands.

edit configure:
Input command "edit_config" or open conf/my.conf by favorite text editor.
Edit configure like below format.
[command_name]
linkto = URL, file path, or special commands

example:
[github]
linkto = http://github.com/

=== special commands ===
 * !version
   * show version information
 * !reload
   * reload configure file
 * !exit
   * exit TeaLauncher
